name: lauronitrile

Lauronitrile has a 10 carbon chain in addition to the initial ethane base, so: 10 CH2 groups * 2 degrees Celsius = +20 degrees Celsius. Additionally, the cyano group (C≡N) is polar and introduces dipole-dipole interactions, but due to the length of the carbon chain, its effect on the melting point is relatively small. Therefore, the cyano group will add another +2 degrees Celsius, considering its polarity and contribution to the molecular rigidity. Thus, the total estimated increase is 20 (for the CH2 groups) + 2 (for the cyano group) degrees Celsius to the base melting point of ethane.
